This paper deals with social learning strategies and their impact on group performance, which falls under the category of social networks and computational social science. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to analyze the data, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential cybersecurity implications of network structures, which makes cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses network analysis and statistical methods, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
